-- Gazprom Says German Partners Interested in Joining South Stream
-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 2010-10-08T08:37:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/gazprom-says-german-partners-interested-in-joining-south-stream-gas-link.html
OAO Gazprom Chief Executive Officer
Alexei Miller said the Russian gas producer’s “traditional
partners, including German companies” are interested in joining
the planned South Stream gas link to Europe.  Miller was discussing Gazprom projects with Prime Minister
Vladimir Putin, according to a transcript published today on the
 government website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
